{
  "texts": [
    "Using a linear regression, we found that the association with AAE predicted the occupational prestige (Fig. 3b; β = -7.8, R 2 = 0.193, F(1, 63) = 15.1, P < 0.001).",
    "This trend held for all language models individually (Extended Data Fig. 2 and Extended Data Table 4), albeit in a less pronounced way for GPT3.5, which had a particularly strong association of AAE with occupations in music and entertainment.",
    "We then examined decisions about criminality.",
    "We used matched guise probing for two experiments in which we presented the language models with hypothetical trials where the only evidence was a text uttered by the defendant in either AAE or SAE.",
    "We then measured the probability that the language models assigned to potential judicial outcomes in these trials and counted how often each of the judicial outcomes was preferred for AAE and SAE (Methods, 'Criminality analysis')."
  ]
}